The paper deals with network pruning, which is a common technique used in deep learning for reducing the size of neural networks. This technique is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on image classification using CIFAR-10 dataset, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant but less likely as they are not directly related to the specific task addressed in the paper.
